<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 16 at 1:57PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Moderate to heavy snow in the southeastern Adirondacks,
western Mohawk valley, Schoharie Valley and northwestern Saratoga
Region...
A band of heavy snow has formed over parts of the southeastern
Adirondacks, western Mohawk Valley, Schoharie Valley and
northwestern Saratoga Region. This band of snow will slowly move
east into the central Mohawk Valley and Lake George Region through
4 PM.
Visibilities will be less than a half mile with brief periods of
near zero visibility. Snowfall rates will be 1 to 3 inches per
hour. Motorists are advised to slow down and allow for extra
distance between yourself and other drivers.</description>
